## 5 Tips to Get Your Urgent Loan Approved Faster

If you need a "Yes" quickly, you can help the lender by being prepared. Even for an urgent loan, no one gives out money without checking a few things.

### 1. Have Your Bank Statements Ready
Almost every lender in Malaysia will want to see your last 3 to 6 months of bank statements. Have the PDFs ready to send. If you provide messy screenshots, it just slows things down.

### 2. Be Honest About Your CTOS/CCRIS
We know that many Malaysian SMEs have "colourful" credit histories. Maybe you missed a payment during MCO, or a previous business partner left you with a mess. Tell us upfront. It’s easier for us to find a solution when we know the full picture than when we find a "surprise" during the background check.

### 3. Know Your Asset Value
If you’re looking for a secured urgent loan, know what your collateral is worth. If it’s a 5-ton lorry or a CNC machine, having the original invoice or a recent valuation saves a lot of time.

### 4. Have a Clear Plan for Repayment
Lenders aren't just looking at why you need the money; they’re looking at how you’ll pay it back. "I need RM50k to buy stock for a confirmed order worth RM120k" is a much better answer than "I just need cash."

### 5. Check the License
This is the most important tip. If a lender asks for "processing fees" upfront before giving you the loan, **walk away**. Real licensed lenders deduct fees from the loan amount; they don't ask you to bank in money to an individual account first.

